message:
Release 0.0.5

Changes:
Moved formik and @material-ui/core to peer dependencies

Release 0.0.6

* Do not ignore disabled prop
chore: Changed react peer dependency to match material ui core

Add MIT license field to package.json (#104)

License already existed, add to metadata

Refactor: Use nullish coalescing operator to simplify undefined checking (#122)

* chore: Upgrade typescript to 3.7.4

* chore: Upgrade prettier to 1.19.1

* refactor: Simplify expression by nullish coalescing operator

Add support for @material-ui/pickers (#115)

This adds DatePicker, KeyboardDatePicker, TimePicker, KeyboardTimePicker, DateTimePicker, KeyboardDateTimePicker

fix #110

Co-authored-by: Ciaran Liedeman <ciaranliedeman@gmail.com>

chore: Use jest global types to avoid storybook build failures (#177)

* chore: Use jest global types to avoid storybook build failures
* chore: updated tsloader
chore: bump material ui dev dep
Update pickers to MUI5 with support for Mobile and Static pickers
Fix npm install by removing unused eslint package

Add missing peer dependencies

+ Adjust test cases
+ Adjust dependency versions
